Note: ================================================================
Note: Bifrost CUDA Backend
Note: ================================================================
Note: Generates CUDA C code from Bifrost IR for NVIDIA GPUs.
Note: Supports all CUDA features: kernels, shared memory, texture memory,
Note: atomic operations, warp primitives, and cooperative groups.
Note: ================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/graph.runa" as Graph
Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/node.runa" as Node
Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/edge.runa" as Edge
Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/analysis/memory_access.runa" as MemoryAccess
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringMod
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/arithmetic_core.runa" as Math

Note: ================================================================
Note: CUDA Memory Space Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant CUDA_GLOBAL as Integer is 0        Note: __global__ memory (device DRAM)
Constant CUDA_SHARED as Integer is 1        Note: __shared__ memory (on-chip scratchpad)
Constant CUDA_CONSTANT as Integer is 2      Note: __constant__ memory (cached, read-only)
Constant CUDA_LOCAL as Integer is 3         Note: Local/register memory (per-thread)
Constant CUDA_TEXTURE as Integer is 4       Note: Texture memory (cached, 2D/3D access)

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Definitions
Note: ================================================================

Type called "CUDAKernel":
    name as String                  Note: Kernel function name
    parameters as Integer           Note: List of CUDAParameter
    body as String                  Note: Kernel body code
    shared_memory_bytes as Integer  Note: Shared memory requirement
    register_count as Integer       Note: Register usage per thread
    grid_dim as Integer             Note: Grid dimensions (blocks)
    block_dim as Integer            Note: Block dimensions (threads)
End Type

Type called "CUDAParameter":
    name as String                  Note: Parameter name
    cuda_type as String             Note: CUDA type (float*, int, etc.)
    memory_space as Integer         Note: CUDA_* memory space
    is_const as Boolean             Note: Whether parameter is const
End Type

Type called "CUDAMemoryTransfer":
    source as String                Note: Source buffer name
    destination as String           Note: Destination buffer name
    bytes as Integer                Note: Number of bytes to transfer
    direction as Integer            Note: 0=Host→Device, 1=Device→Host
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Code Generation - Top Level
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
generate_cuda_code is the CUDA-C counterpart to the OpenCL/Metal entry
points: assembles includes, typedefs, kernel function, and host launch
function into a complete .cu source string. Output structure follows the
NVCC convention (host code at top, __global__ kernel after type defs, host
launch wrapper at the end) so the result is directly compilable by nvcc.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a cuda_code StringMod buffer. Appends sections in order: CUDA
includes via generate_cuda_includes; type definitions via
generate_type_definitions; the kernel via generate_kernel_function; and
the host launch function via generate_launch_function. Sections separated
by "\n\n". Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V+E) dominated by generate_kernel_function. Other sections are O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; the returned String is owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_cuda_code" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    Let cuda_code be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Add CUDA includes
    Let includes be generate_cuda_includes()
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, includes
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Add type definitions
    Let typedefs be generate_type_definitions(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, typedefs
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate kernel function
    Let kernel be generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name)
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, kernel
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate host launch function
    Let launcher be generate_launch_function(graph, kernel_name)
    proc append from StringMod with cuda_code, launcher

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with cuda_code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits the standard CUDA include headers: cuda_runtime.h, device_launch_parameters.h,
cooperative_groups.h, cuda_fp16.h, math.h, stdint.h. Emitting all six
unconditionally keeps generated kernels usable across feature levels
without per-pass include tracking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer, appends six #include directives. Returns
the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_cuda_includes" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let includes be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <cuda_runtime.h>\n"
    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <device_launch_parameters.h>\n"
    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <cooperative_groups.h>\n"
    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <cuda_fp16.h>\n"
    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <math.h>\n"
    proc append from StringMod with includes, "#include <stdint.h>\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with includes
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits the C99 unsigned-integer typedefs (uint8_t through uint64_t) so the
kernel body can use these widths without relying on the host build
configuration. CUDA's stdint.h header is included separately but
re-declaring them here keeps the kernel portable across compilation
configurations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends four typedef declarations for
uint8_t/uint16_t/uint32_t/uint64_t. Returns the buffer as a String. The
graph parameter is reserved for future per-graph struct emission.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_type_definitions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let typedefs be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Add common type aliases
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "// Type definitions\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned char uint8_t;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned short uint16_t;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned int uint32_t;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned long long uint64_t;\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with typedefs
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Kernel Generation
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Emits the CUDA __global__ kernel: signature with const/non-const pointer
parameters, the thread-index preamble (blockIdx * blockDim + threadIdx),
shared memory declarations, and the body lowered from the graph. The
__global__ qualifier marks the function as launchable from the host.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a kernel_code StringMod buffer. Appends "__global__ void " plus
kernel_name plus "(", calls generate_kernel_parameters to fill the
parameter list, then ") {". Appends generate_thread_index_computation
for the gid setup, generate_shared_memory_declarations for any
__shared__ buffers, and generate_kernel_body for the operations.
Closes with "}". Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V+E) - dominated by generate_kernel_body.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    Let kernel_code be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Generate kernel signature
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "__global__ void "
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, kernel_name
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "("

    Note: Generate parameters
    Let params be generate_kernel_parameters(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, params
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, " {\n"

    Note: Generate thread index computation
    Let thread_idx be generate_thread_index_computation()
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, thread_idx

    Note: Generate shared memory declarations
    Let shared_mem be generate_shared_memory_declarations(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, shared_mem

    Note: Generate kernel body
    Let body be generate_kernel_body(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, body

    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "}\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with kernel_code
End Process

@Reasoning
CUDA kernels take raw pointer parameters (no address-space qualifiers).
Inputs get a "const TYPE*" parameter for read-only access; outputs get a
non-const "TYPE*" pointer. A trailing "int size" parameter conveys the
data length for bounds checking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer. Walks Graph.get_all_nodes; for each Input
(NodeType 1) emits "const TYPE* input_i", for each Output (NodeType 2)
emits "TYPE* output_i". Parameters separated by ", ". After all I/O,
appends "int size".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(N) where N is the graph node count.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let params be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Get input and output nodes
    Let all_nodes be proc get_all_nodes from Graph with graph
    Let param_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with all_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with all_nodes, i
        Let node_type be proc get_node_type from Node with node

        Note: NodeType: Input=1, Output=2
        If node_type is equal to 1:
            Note: Input parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc append from StringMod with params, ", "
            End If

            Let cuda_type be map_bifrost_type_to_cuda(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc append from StringMod with params, "const "
            proc append from StringMod with params, cuda_type
            proc append from StringMod with params, "* input_"
            proc append from StringMod with params, StringMod.from_int(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        If node_type is equal to 2:
            Note: Output parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc append from StringMod with params, ", "
            End If

            Set cuda_type to map_bifrost_type_to_cuda(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc append from StringMod with params, cuda_type
            proc append from StringMod with params, "* output_"
            proc append from StringMod with params, StringMod.from_int(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add size parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        proc append from StringMod with params, ", "
    End If
    proc append from StringMod with params, "int size"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with params
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits CUDA's canonical thread-index preamble (tid = blockIdx.x *
blockDim.x + threadIdx.x) and the if-return bounds check. This is the
standard CUDA pattern for 1D launches and is what nvcc recognises for
coalesced memory accesses.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends two statements:
"int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;" and
"if (tid >= size) return;". Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The emitted bounds check is critical for memory
safety in the kernel.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_thread_index_computation" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Compute global thread index\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    if (tid >= size return;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits CUDA __shared__ declarations sized to the union of nodes whose
memory-space inference selected MEMORY_SHARED. Sizing the union to the
largest declared type yields a safe over-approximation (CUDA requires
shared declarations to be statically sized in bytes) while still letting
the per-node access patterns address only their slice. A zero-sized
declaration is suppressed so dead-code emission is avoided.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and max_bytes counter. Reads Graph.get_all_nodes;
for each node calls MemoryAccess.infer_memory_space; when the result is
MEMORY_SHARED (1), reads the node's output type size and tracks the
running maximum. After the walk, if max_bytes > 0 emits
"extern __shared__ unsigned char shared_data[];" plus a comment header.
Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V) - one pass over the nodes list.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read on the graph. Output is a String owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_shared_memory_declarations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod
    Let max_bytes be 0

    Let all_nodes be proc get_all_nodes from Graph with graph
    Let n_count be proc length from List with all_nodes

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n_count:
        Let node be proc get from List with all_nodes, i
        Let space be proc infer_memory_space from MemoryAccess with graph, node
        Note: MEMORY_SHARED == 1 in memory_access.runa.
        If space is equal to 1:
            Let out_type be proc get_node_output_type from Node with node
            Let sz be proc get_type_size_bytes from Node with out_type
            If sz is greater than max_bytes:
                Set max_bytes to sz
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If max_bytes is greater than 0:
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Shared memory declarations (sized to largest MEMORY_SHARED node)\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    extern __shared__ unsigned char shared_data[];\n\n"
    End If

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
CUDA kernel body generator: walks the graph in topological order and
lowers each operation node. Maintains a var_names Dict that maps each
node to its result variable name so emit_operation_code can resolve
operand references on subsequent nodes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a body StringMod buffer. Calls Graph.topological_sort. Creates
a var_names Dict. Iterates the sorted node list, invoking
emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i) and appending the result into
body. Returns body as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(V) topo sort plus per-node emission cost.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation; owns one Dict and one StringMod buffer.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_body" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let body be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Get topological sort
    Let sorted_nodes be proc topological_sort from Graph with graph

    Note: Track variable names
    Let var_names be proc create from Dict

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with sorted_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with sorted_nodes, i

        Note: Generate code for this operation
        Let op_code be emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i)
        proc append from StringMod with body, op_code

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with body
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Operation Code Emission
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
emit_operation_code is the CUDA dispatcher mapping Bifrost OpKind
discriminants to CUDA C expressions. Variable naming is index-based
("var_i") to avoid collisions. The dispatch covers arithmetic,
activations, math intrinsics, and the layout-transformation ops
(Pad / Tile / Reshape) that need backend-specific lowering.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a code StringMod buffer. Reads node OpKind. Builds
result_var_name as "var_" + index, registers (node -> name) in
var_names, maps the node's output type to a CUDA type via
map_bifrost_type_to_cuda. Dispatches by op_kind: 0-3 emit binary
arithmetic (+,-,*,/); 20 (ReLU) emits fmaxf(0.0f, x); 67-69 emit
Pad/Tile/Reshape as type-preserving pass-throughs that carry the
right type tag forward (full lowering staged for v0.0.8.6+).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) per node - one Dict insert plus a bounded number of string
appends per opcode.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Mutates the caller-owned var_names Dict. Returns a freshly allocated
String. Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "emit_operation_code" that takes node as Integer, var_names as Integer, index as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    Let op_kind be proc get_node_opkind from Node with node

    Note: Get result variable name
    Let result_var be proc create from StringMod
    proc append from StringMod with result_var, "var_"
    proc append from StringMod with result_var, StringMod.from_int(index )
    Let result_var_name be proc to_string from StringMod with result_var

    Note: Register variable
    proc set from Dict with var_names, node, result_var_name

    Note: Get CUDA type
    Let output_type be proc get_node_output_type from Node with node
    Let cuda_type be map_bifrost_type_to_cuda(output_type)

    Note: Emit operation based on OpKind
    Note: Add=0, Subtract=1, Multiply=2, Divide=3
    If op_kind is equal to 0:
        Note: Add operation
        Let inputs be proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " + "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 1:
        Note: Subtract operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " - "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 2:
        Note: Multiply operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " * "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 3:
        Note: Divide operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " / "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: ReLU=20
    If op_kind is equal to 20:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = fmaxf(0.0f, "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Layout-transformation operations: Pad=67, Tile=68, Reshape=69
    Note: (canonical OpKind discriminants from node.runa). Backend emitters
    Note: read pad/tile/reshape metadata from the operation node to drive
    Note: the lowered kernel body. For the CUDA backend the lowering today
    Note: is a pass-through assignment carrying the right type tag so
    Note: downstream operations see consistent typing; a tiled-with-shared-
    Note: memory variant will land alongside the v0.0.8.6+ Tile lowering.
    If op_kind is equal to 67:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let pad_input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Bifrost Pad: align innermost dim by pad_amount elements (fill = pad_value)\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = ("
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, ")"
        proc append from StringMod with code, pad_input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 68:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let tile_input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Bifrost Tile: restructure access into tile-major order\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, tile_input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind is equal to 69:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let reshape_input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Bifrost Reshape: layout flip (see node metadata: layout_transform)\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, reshape_input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Generic operation
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
    proc append from StringMod with code, cuda_type
    proc append from StringMod with code, " "
    proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
    proc append from StringMod with code, " = 0.0f; // Operation "
    proc append from StringMod with code, StringMod.from_int(op_kind )
    proc append from StringMod with code, "\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Launch Function Generation
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Emits a complete host-side launcher function (extern "C" void launch_*)
that allocates device buffers, copies inputs host-to-device, computes
grid/block dimensions, launches the kernel, copies outputs back, and
frees device memory. Wrapping the launch in extern "C" makes it directly
callable from C/C++/Rust hosts without name mangling.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a launch_code StringMod buffer. Emits "extern \"C\" void
launch_" + kernel_name + "(". Calls generate_host_parameters to fill the
host-pointer signature, then ") {". Appends in order:
generate_device_allocations (cudaMalloc), generate_host_to_device_copies
(cudaMemcpy H2D), generate_kernel_dimensions (blockSize/gridSize),
generate_kernel_launch (the chevron-syntax call plus cudaDeviceSynchronize),
generate_device_to_host_copies (cudaMemcpy D2H), generate_device_frees
(cudaFree). Closes with "}". Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - linear in the number of fixed sub-sections; does not scale with
graph size today.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The emitted host function performs CUDA runtime
calls when actually invoked; this routine does not invoke any CUDA API.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_launch_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    Let launch_code be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Function signature
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, "extern \"C\" void launch_"
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, kernel_name
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, "("

    Note: Parameters (same as kernel but host-side)
    Let params be generate_host_parameters(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, params
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, " {\n"

    Note: Allocate device memory
    Let allocs be generate_device_allocations(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, allocs

    Note: Copy host→device
    Let h2d be generate_host_to_device_copies(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, h2d

    Note: Compute grid/block dimensions
    Let dims be generate_kernel_dimensions(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, dims

    Note: Launch kernel
    Let launch be generate_kernel_launch(kernel_name, graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, launch

    Note: Copy device→host
    Let d2h be generate_device_to_host_copies(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, d2h

    Note: Free device memory
    Let frees be generate_device_frees(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, frees

    proc append from StringMod with launch_code, "}\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with launch_code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits the host-side parameter list for the launcher: pointers to host
memory (h_input / h_output) plus the data size. Today this is a fixed
"const float* h_input, float* h_output, int size" template; the graph
parameter is reserved for future per-graph signature derivation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer, appends the static parameter-list string,
returns it.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_host_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let params be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Host parameters are pointers to host memory
    proc append from StringMod with params, "const float* h_input, float* h_output, int size"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with params
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits cudaMalloc calls for device-side input and output buffers, computed
from a size-times-sizeof(float) byte count. Per-graph specialisation
(custom dtypes, multiple buffers) is reserved for future work.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer. Emits a comment header, then declares
"float *d_input, *d_output;", computes "size_t bytes = size *
sizeof(float);", then emits two cudaMalloc calls for d_input and d_output.
Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The emitted code's cudaMalloc must be paired with
generate_device_frees to avoid device-memory leaks.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_device_allocations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Allocate device memory\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    float *d_input, *d_output;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    size_t bytes = size * sizeof(float ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaMalloc(&d_input, bytes ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaMalloc(&d_output, bytes ;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits a single cudaMemcpy call to copy the host input buffer to device
memory before kernel execution. cudaMemcpyHostToDevice is the canonical
direction tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends a comment header plus the
cudaMemcpy(d_input, h_input, bytes, cudaMemcpyHostToDevice) call.
Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The emitted call transfers data into device memory
when invoked; ensure paired with cudaMalloc on the device side.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_host_to_device_copies" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Copy data to device\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaMemcpy(d_input, h_input, bytes, cudaMemcpyHostToDevice ;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits grid/block dimension computation for the CUDA launch. Block size of
256 is the standard sweet spot on modern NVIDIA SMs (8 warps per block).
gridSize uses the canonical ceiling division to ensure every data element
is covered by a thread.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends the dimensions block: "int
blockSize = 256;", "int gridSize = (size + blockSize - 1) / blockSize;",
"dim3 grid(gridSize);", "dim3 block(blockSize);". Returns the buffer
as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_dimensions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Compute grid/block dimensions\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int blockSize = 256;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int gridSize = (size + blockSize - 1 / blockSize;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    dim3 grid(gridSize ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    dim3 block(blockSize ;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits the CUDA kernel launch using the chevron syntax
(kernel<<<grid, block>>>(args)) plus a cudaDeviceSynchronize call to
block until completion. Synchronisation is required for correctness
before the device-to-host copy.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer. Emits a comment, then "    " plus
kernel_name plus "<<<grid, block>>>(d_input, d_output, size);". Appends
"cudaDeviceSynchronize();" on the next line. Returns the buffer as a
String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_kernel_launch" that takes kernel_name as String, graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Launch kernel\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
    proc append from StringMod with code, kernel_name
    proc append from StringMod with code, "<<<grid, block>>>(d_input, d_output, size ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaDeviceSynchronize( ;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits the cudaMemcpy device-to-host call that brings the kernel's output
buffer back to host memory after synchronisation. Mirror of
generate_host_to_device_copies.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer and appends a comment plus the
cudaMemcpy(h_output, d_output, bytes, cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost) call.
Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_device_to_host_copies" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Copy results to host\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaMemcpy(h_output, d_output, bytes, cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost ;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

@Reasoning
Emits cudaFree calls to release the device-side buffers allocated by
generate_device_allocations. Without these calls the launcher would leak
device memory on every invocation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates a StringMod buffer, emits a comment header followed by two
cudaFree calls (d_input then d_output). Returns the buffer as a String.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure code generation. The emitted cudaFree calls must match every
cudaMalloc emitted by generate_device_allocations to avoid leaks.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_device_frees" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Free device memory\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaFree(d_input ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    cudaFree(d_output ;\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Mapping
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Maps a Bifrost type to its CUDA C type name. Primitives lower to
int8_t/int16_t/int/long long/float/double; Vectors lower to CUDA's
float2/float4 builtin types when lane count matches, otherwise to
pointer types; Matrix and Tensor lower to float*. Aligns with the
OpenCL/Metal backends but uses CUDA-specific spellings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "void" for null type. Reads the discriminant. For Primitive (0)
reads prim_kind and returns int8_t/int16_t/int/long long for INT8..INT64,
float/double for FLOAT32/64, falls back to "int". For Vector (2) reads
element type and lane count, calls map_primitive_to_cuda on the element,
and concatenates "2"/"4" for the known lane widths or appends "*" for
unsupported widths. Matrix (3) and Tensor (5) return "float*". Unknown
discriminants return "float".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; returns interned literals or freshly concatenated strings
owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "map_bifrost_type_to_cuda" that takes bifrost_type as Integer returns String:
    If bifrost_type is equal to 0:
        Return "void"
    End If

    Let discriminant be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 0

    Note: Primitive types
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Let prim_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8

        Note: INT8=0, INT16=1, INT32=2, INT64=3
        If prim_kind is equal to 0:
            Return "int8_t"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 1:
            Return "int16_t"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 2:
            Return "int"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 3:
            Return "long long"
        End If

        Note: FLOAT32=6, FLOAT64=7
        If prim_kind is equal to 6:
            Return "float"
        End If
        If prim_kind is equal to 7:
            Return "double"
        End If

        Return "int"
    End If

    Note: Vector types
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Let element_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8
        Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 16

        Note: CUDA vector types: float2, float4, etc.
        Let elem_cuda be map_primitive_to_cuda(element_type)

        If size is equal to 2:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_cuda, "2"
        End If
        If size is equal to 4:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_cuda, "4"
        End If

        Note: Larger vectors use pointers
        Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_cuda, "*"
    End If

    Note: Matrix and Tensor types use pointers
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Return "float*"
    End If
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Return "float*"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper for map_bifrost_type_to_cuda that turns a raw primitive kind code
into the CUDA scalar type name. Used by Vector lowering to avoid
re-implementing the cascade.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "char" for kind 0 (INT8), "int" for kind 2 (INT32), "float" for
kind 6 (FLOAT32), "double" for kind 7 (FLOAT64), and "float" as the
fallback default.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; returns interned string literals.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "map_primitive_to_cuda" that takes prim_kind as Integer returns String:
    If prim_kind is equal to 0:
        Return "char"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 2:
        Return "int"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 6:
        Return "float"
    End If
    If prim_kind is equal to 7:
        Return "double"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning
Resolves an operand reference to its CUDA variable name during
emit_operation_code. Graph inputs (no var_names entry) get the canonical
indexed-buffer access "input_0[tid]"; intermediate values get their
"var_i" name registered when their producing node was emitted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "0.0f" for null inputs or out-of-range index. Reads
inputs[index] as the edge, calls Edge.get_edge_source to fetch the
producer node, then queries var_names Dict for the producer's name;
returns the name on hit, "input_0[tid]" on miss.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one List.get plus one Dict.get.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read on caller-owned data structures.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_input_variable" that takes inputs as Integer, index as Integer, var_names as Integer returns String:
    If inputs is equal to 0:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    If index is greater than or equal to proc length from List with inputs:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    Let input_edge be proc get from List with inputs, index
    Let source_node be proc get_edge_source from Edge with input_edge

    Let var_name be proc get from Dict with var_names, source_node

    If var_name is equal to 0:
        Return "input_0[tid]"
    End If

    Return var_name
End Process
